# UCAB - User Flow

## Overview

The User Flow represents the sequence of steps a user follows while interacting with the UCAB Cab Booking System. It helps visualize the journey from user registration to ride completion.

---

## Objective

To define the workflow of the UCAB application and demonstrate how users interact with different modules of the system.

---

## User Flow Steps

### Step 1: User Registration/Login

- User opens the application.
- Registers a new account or logs into an existing account.

### Step 2: Search for Cab

- Enter pickup location.
- Enter destination.
- View available cab options.

### Step 3: Book Ride

- Select preferred cab.
- Confirm booking request.

### Step 4: Driver Assignment

- System finds nearby available driver.
- Driver accepts the ride request.

### Step 5: Ride Tracking

- User tracks driver location.
- Driver navigates to pickup location.

### Step 6: Ride Starts

- Driver picks up passenger.
- Ride status changes to "Started".

### Step 7: Ride Completion

- Driver reaches destination.
- Ride status changes to "Completed".

### Step 8: Payment

- User completes payment.
- Receipt is generated.

### Step 9: Ride History

- Ride details are stored.
- User can view booking history anytime.

---

